<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="../dist/shared.css">
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy" content="default-src 'self' https:; base-uri 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; object-src 'none'; connect-src 'self' https:; img-src 'self' data: https:; font-src 'self' data: https:; script-src 'self' https: 'unsafe-hashes'; script-src-attr 'unsafe-hashes'; style-src 'self' https: 'unsafe-hashes'; style-src-attr 'unsafe-hashes'">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Interactive Accordion UI</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="acc.css">
</head>

<body>

  <div class="accordion-container">

    <div class="title">
      <h1>Interactive Accordion</h1>
      <p>Modern Glassmorphism FAQ Interface</p>
    </div>

    <!-- ITEM 1 -->

    <div class="accordion-item active">

      <button class="accordion-btn">
        <span>+</span>
        What is HTML?
      </button>

      <div class="accordion-content" style="max-height:200px;">
        <p>
          HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the standard language used
          to structure and create web pages. It defines headings, text,
          images, links, forms, and page layouts.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- ITEM 2 -->

    <div class="accordion-item">

      <button class="accordion-btn">
        <span>+</span>
        What is CSS?
      </button>

      <div class="accordion-content">
        <p>
          CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is used to style web pages by
          controlling layouts, colors, fonts, spacing, animations,
          responsiveness, and visual effects.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- ITEM 3 -->

    <div class="accordion-item">

      <button class="accordion-btn">
        <span>+</span>
        What is JavaScript?
      </button>

      <div class="accordion-content">
        <p>
          JavaScript adds interactivity and dynamic behavior to websites,
          enabling features like sliders, form validation, animations,
          popups, API integration, and real-time updates.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- ITEM 4 -->

    <div class="accordion-item">

      <button class="accordion-btn">
        <span>+</span>
        Why use Accordion UI?
      </button>

      <div class="accordion-content">
        <p>
          Accordion components help organize content efficiently by
          allowing users to expand and collapse sections, improving
          readability and saving screen space.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>

  <script src="acc.js"></script>
    <script src="../dist/shared.js"></script>
</body>
</html>